<TEXT>
president bush joked to an audience of radio 
and television correspondents thursday night that he got even with 
the iranians for a phony phone call from president hashemi 
rafsanjani 
your broadcasts hit me pretty hard a while back about a guy 
claiming to be rafsanjani a little confusion with the phone 
call bush told the broadcasters 
today i got him back called him up and asked if he had prince 
abdul in a can said bush to laughter from the crowd of more than 
2000 but then i forgot how to say let him out in farsi 
bush said he had also got a call from a very upset lech 
walesa the solidarity leader 
he heard me say at the last press conference that i have no 
faith in polls the president quipped 
the annual blacktie dinner of the radio and television 
correspondents association drew leaders of congress and top 
administration officials as well as broadcast executives and 
journalists 
for the second time in five nights the president and barbara 
bush watched impressionist jim morris do his sendup of bush 
ronald reagan and other politicians 
the bushes had originally planned to leave before morris act 
but they decided to stay 
theres something in the constitution about cruel and unusual 
punishment but we had planned to leave but i want to hear this 
thing one more time said bush barbara likes his act 
then mocking his own disjuncted speaking style that morris and 
other mimics love to imitate bush said ill be honest hes 
good too good thats as far as ill go not going to comment 
not going to criticize jim morris at this juncture wouldnt be 
prudent 
the bushes laughed along with most of the jokes told by morris 
and talk show host larry king who served as interlocutor 
reporters asked mrs bush walking pet dog millie upon her 
return to the white house if she had had her fill of jim morris 
yet 
havent you she replied 
