the san jose mercury news won top 
honors in the 1990 national headliner clubs 56th annual 
competition for coverage of the california earthquake 
the newspaper won first place in the category of news reporting 
in daily newspapers with a circulation greater than 150000 for its 
earthquake coverage last october the awards panel announced monday 
the arizona republic won the best investigative reporting award 
for the phoenix newspapers coverage of the collapse of charles 
keatings savings and loan empire 
the seattle postintelligencer won the outstanding public 
service award for a series written by james a wallace that exposed 
the health dangers posed by transporting poisonous materials in 
large tank trucks 
the fort worth texas startelegram received a special citation 
for creating extraordinary local involvement and pride with its 
coverage of the van cliburn international piano competition 
the press club of atlantic city sponsors of the award 
competition is to present the honors at a dinner may 12 this 
