hundreds of chanting aids activists besieged 
the state capitol on wednesday wrapping parts of the historic 
building in red tape and chanting slogans police arrested 80 
people 
the demonstrators blocked entrances to the capitol and marched 
through the hallways to preselected areas where they fell to the 
floor or otherwise disrupted government operations 
police dragged dozens of demonstrators away to waiting paddy 
wagons some had handcuffed themselves together and police used 
boltcutters to separate them 
by the time police escorted the last demonstrator into a waiting 
bus wednesday evening there were 80 arrests most were charged 
with disorderly conduct said said thomas tubbs spokesman for the 
state office of general services 
one man was charged with harrassment for pushing a police 
officer and a woman was charged with criminal mischief for 
spraypainting slogans on the capitol steps tubbs said 
no police were injured one arrested demonstrator was treated at 
a hospital for a head injury and released tubbs said 
earlier members of the new york citybased aids coalition to 
unleash power or act up picketed the executive mansion they 
shouted down gov mario cuomo when he tried to speak to them 
were closing down this capitol walter kawandler of new 
york city said as he and about two dozen others sprawled on the 
