really only skindeep william kinard chief scientist for the 
ldef said on wednesday 
a nasa study concluded recently that the proposed space station 
freedom would begin falling apart before completion and would need 
extensive maintenance in space but kinard said the space lab had 
fared well in space boding well for freedom 
all of our systems have survived better i think than predicted 
so you might expect the same thing from the space station he 
said the survivability of materials and systems in space is 
pretty good 
kinard said concern about freedom is healthy but problems of 
duration in space can be resolved the space station is expected to 
cost 30 billion by the time its completed and manned in 1999 
weve built a lot of spacecraft that have performed for long 
periods of time in space he said the data should give one 
confidence that you can design spacecraft and have them work 
the ldef satellite was placed in orbit in april 1984 for an 
expected 10 months because of delays however it was not 
retrieved until jan 12 when astronauts snared it 200 miles out in 
space 
the six years were the longest time a spacecraft had been in 
space before being retrieved for study none of the experiments 
were lost during the long stay 
barring a rescue the laboratory would have come crashing down 
through the atmosphere in midmarch and all the experiments 
attached to its exterior would have been lost if not for gravity 
the structure could have lasted many more years in space although 
some of the experiments might have decayed kinard said 
</TEXT>
