<TEXT>
a federal judge ruled the citys method of 
electing council members illegal and ordered new elections as soon 
as possible to offer better representation to blacks and hispanics 
us district judge jerry buchmeyers ruling wednesday gives the 
nations eighthbiggest city 30 days to submit a plan for the 
special interim election the judge did not set an election date 
buchmeyer said he wanted an election plan with 11 to 15 
singlemember districts and a mayor elected at large 
eight council members are currently elected in singlemember 
districts while three including the mayor are elected atlarge 
although 51 percent of the citys more than 1 million residents 
are black or hispanic only two council members are black there 
are no hispanic council members 
the 83 system for electing members of the city council 
violates the voting rights act because it dilutes the votes of 
politically cohesive blacks and hispanics in dallas buchmeyer 
ruled 
under the 83 system africanamericans and hispanics are 
denied access to the three atlarge seats because they cannot raise 
from their own communities the enormous amount of money that is 
required for an effective atlarge city campaign in dallas 
buchmeyer said an interim election would end once and for all 
the atlarge election of all city council members 
only the mayor would be elected at large buchmeyer said 
if the city fails to develop an interim election plan within 30 
days buchmeyer would devise a courtordered one said betsy 
julian executive director of the legal services of north texas 
mayor annette strauss refused to comment on the ruling until she 
had studied it 
the plaintiffs including two former unsuccessful black council 
candidates claimed the only way to achieve racial equality in the 
elections was to have all members of the council elected in single 
districts 
the city had countered with a 1041 plan which it scheduled to 
go into effect in 1991 under which voters would elect 10 council 
members from individual districts four from regional quadrants and 
the mayor at large 
the judge suggests that the 1041 system has the same problem 
as the 83 system said the plaintiffs lawyer mike daniel 
the suit was filed by the two candidates roy williams and 
marvin crenshaw in may 1988 they later were joined by the 
ledbetter neighborhood association a hispanic group 
