<TEXT>
special kgb guards who protect president mikhail 
s gorbachev and other leaders have stopped wouldbe assassins who 
tried to enter government buildings with sawedoff shotguns and 
knives a news report said today 
every month our men in the kremlin on red square and other 
places expose and detain about a dozen people with criminal 
intentions a kgb general yuri s plekhanov told the communist 
party daily pravda 
even in the period of gorbachevs policy of greater openness 
officials previously have not discussed planned attacks on top 
leaders 
several weeks ago a popular tv show referred to an effort to 
assassinate president leonid i brezhnev in 1969 the effort had 
previously only been rumored to have occurred 
security for gorbachev compared to that for leaders of other 
major countries is erratic 
when the soviet leader traveled to washington in 1987 to meet 
president reagan us security officers said gorbachevs security 
operated in nearly an identical way 
but gorbachevs security details have appeared ragged on other 
foreign trips and at times in moscow security for gorbachev and 
his wife raisa appears to be lax 
gorbachev who enjoys stepping into crowds to chat with people 
in the soviet union and abroad presents a tougher security problem 
than previous soviet leaders whose public appearances had little 
spontaneity 
plekhanov said that kgb security guards for the soviet 
leadership have not had to use their weapons since world war ii 
the kgb general said that recently a man waiting in the 
reception room of the communist party central committee pulled out 
a sawedoff shotgun but he was disarmed by kgb maj v frolov 
gorbachev is said to do most of his daytoday work in the 
central committee headquarters although a person visiting the 
reception area would be unlikely to get anywhere close to the 
soviet leader 
others with bombs knives and guns have been arrested on red 
square and in the kremlin he said 
last year security guards found a knife on a person among the 
crowd entering the kremlin for new years festivities 
a person was arrested with a bomb on may 1 the may day holiday 
in red square where the entire soviet leadership gathers atop 
lenins mausoleum to review a workers parade 
the next day security agents on red square arrested a man with 
a gun that accidentally went off when he was being detained 
plekhanov said 
besides gorbachev the guard unit protects other soviet leaders 
provides security for parliamentary sessions in the kremlin and 
cooperates with the secret services of other countries during the 
visits of foreign dignitaries 
the kgb guards have good contacts with scotland yard the us 
secret service finnish west germany and other security police he 
said 
without going into specifics plekhanov said the kgb guard is 
relatively small and cooperates with other branches of the soviet 
security police during important political events or if it catches 
wind of a plot 
