karl brown a pioneering hollywood 
cinematographer who worked on dw griffiths 1915 silent film epic 
the birth of a nation has died he was 93 
brown died sunday at the motion picture and television hospital 
in woodland hills the cause of death was not disclosed 
in the early days of hollywood brown worked as a 
cinematographers assistant on the birth of a nation and 
intolerance another historical extravaganza made a year later 
by griffith 
brown created the technique of doubleprinting that gave a 
supernatural radiance to christ in intolerance he also helped 
develop the miniature projection process that magnified models into 
monsters for such pictures as king kong 
he directed the 1927 film his dog for cecil b demille 
browns screenplay credits included brewsters millions 
one glorious day ruggles of red gap merton of the 
movies and the pony express 
