a tv documentary identified four people it said 
were responsible for ira bombings that killed 21 people and a 
british lawmaker said new evidence should lead to the release of 
the six people who were convicted 
the home office responsible for law enforcement said in a 
statement today that all four people identified on the television 
program had been investigated by police and that the program does 
not put forward new evidence 
chris mullin a member of the opposition labor party said 
wednesday that those convicted known as the birmingham six were 
innocent of the 1974 bombings of two pubs he said an irish 
republican army informer identified one of the bombers but that 
police failed to follow up the lead 
the lie cannot be sustained much longer mullin told a news 
conference to publicize the third edition of his book on the case 
error of judgment 
the bombings in the northern city of birmingham which also left 
