<TEXT>
a coalition of national groups called thursday 
for steppedup government research on aging to fight the illnesses 
that rob the elderly of their independence 
the task force for aging research funding said the nation is 
pouring increasing amounts of money into sick care for older 
americans while it fails to adequately finance research to help the 
elderly stay healthy 
the coalition called for federal spending of 1 billion a year 
on aging research bringing the spending level up to par with that 
for other major health concerns such as cancer aids and heart 
research 
the alliance for aging research which is leading the coalition 
issued a report warning that the gaps in federal research are 
placing the successful aging and independence of older americans at 
risk 
the successes in health and medicine in the 20th century have 
primarily saved lives in youth and middle age it said 
advances affecting the cure and prevention of chronic illnesses 
in late life have been few 
john l steffens the alliances chairman and president and 
chief executive officer of merrill lynch consumer markets said the 
nation pays a heavy price for its inability to cure or prevent 
alzheimers disease osteoporosis urinary incontinence breast 
cancer arthritis and other conditions that affect the elderly 
research that will help us avoid these illnesses and the costs 
they bring is the most effective investment we can make steffens 
said 
ed truschke president of the alzheimers association said 
alzheimers alone costs the nation more than 90 billion a year 
yet the government spends just 130 million a year seeking a cure 
research is the only way to control the skyrocketing cost of 
alzheimers disease he said 
the alliance report said that as the baby boom generation turns 
into the senior boom in the next century older americans will 
account for onehalf of a health care bill approaching 2 trillion 
a year 
americans age 65 and older represent more than 12 percent of the 
population and those 85 and older represent the fastestgrowing 
segment of the population by 2020 the over65 population is 
expected to more than double to more than 65 million the report 
said 
