<TEXT>
three small aftershocks from last months 
jarring earthquake shook the area early wednesday but no damage 
was reported authorities said 
the aftershocks were centered five miles northwest of upland 
the first two registered 24 on the richter scale and struck at 
636 am and 638 am five hours later 23magnitude tremor was 
recorded said robert finn spokesman for the california institute 
of technology in pasadena 
the feb 28 magnitude 55 quake jolted most of southern 
california but caused only isolated damage it has been followed by 
hundreds of aftershocks 
upland is east of los angeles in western san bernardino county 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude 
an earthquake of magnitude 35 can cause slight damage in the 
local area 4 can cause moderate damage 5 considerable damage and 
6 severe damage 
