civic forum the movement that led the november revolution 
reminded the nation during the televised debate that there were 
more crucial issues facing the nation 
there is no connection between the name of the country and its 
quality he said 
but deputy premier josef hromadka suggested it was a matter of 
supreme importance 
when an agreement is not reached in the election of a pope 
he said the rules say that there should be a oneday break but 
nobody is permitted to leave the conclave and they may take there 
only bread and water to search their conscience 
 
