<TEXT>
parliament moved to end a 123year ban 
on abortions thursday by voting to allow abortion during the first 
12 weeks of pregnancy if the woman is deemed to be in distress 
the senate approved the bill last november and it now must be 
signed into law by king baudouin 
that would leave ireland as the only european community nation 
with a total ban on abortions 
the house of representatives voted 126 to 69 with 12 
abstentions to scrap an 1867 law that made abortion a criminal 
offense and provided terms of up to five years in prison for 
offenders 
that law has been spottily enforced in recent years belgian 
women have been getting abortions for years with little 
interference from authorities also many traveled outside belgium 
to have abortions 
thursdays vote split prime minister wilfried martens 
centerleft coalition along christian democraticsocialist lines 
but coalition partners agreed beforehand the vote would not result 
in a government crisis 
church officials in in this overwhelmingly catholic country 
vigorously opposed the bill though opinion polls indicated most 
belgians feel abortion should be decriminalized 
under the new measure a woman can get an abortion during the 
first 12 weeks of pregnancy if she and her doctor feel she is in 
distress due to the pregnancy 
opponents attacked the term distress as too vague creating 
a situation of abortion on demand 
conservative legislator annemie neyts who supported the bill 
said i have trouble with claims saying the bill is the dawn of 
an age of moral depravation 
christian democrat paul hermans who opposed the measure said 
supporters considered the fetus an inferior being which merits 
only inferior protection 
the government of flanders belgiums dutchspeaking northern 
half meanwhile granted 51 million in subsidies for an 
information campaign on preventing undesired pregnancies 
over the last 20 years the abortion issue became a bitter 
political fight thousands took to the streets in the 1970s over 
the issue 
protests heated up in 1973 when a doctor was jailed for more 
than a month accused of performing hundreds of abortions he was 
later released 
the bill approved thursday capped a 16year period in which more 
than a dozen proabortion bills were voted down in parliament 
</TEXT>
