<DOCNO> AP900329-0170 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
astronomers have identified for the first time 
what they believe is a brown dwarf star a stellar body that lacks 
the mass to trigger the fusion reaction that gives stars their 
brilliant light 
the national science foundation announced thursday that philip 
a ianna of the university of virginia and michael s bessell of 
the stromlo and siding spring observatories in australia identified 
the candidate brown dwarf after taking measurements of its 
brightness and mass 
visible only in the skies of the southern hemisphere the dim 
red stellar body equals about 5 percent of the mass of the sun the 
sun emits about 4000 times more light than the dwarf 
the dwarf is in the milky way the galaxy which includes the 
sun and is about 68 lightyears away the astronomers said a 
lightyear is the distance light travels in a year a bit less than 
6 trillion miles 
brown dwarfs have been theorized to exist for years with most 
experts predicting they would have 7 percent to 8 percent of the 
mass of the sun 
this would not be sufficient mass for gravitational forces to 
compress it and heat it to the point where its hydrogen fuses into 
helium without fusion such a stellar body would give off only a 
faint red glow caused by its modest gravitational compression 
ianna and bessell said they found the candidate brown dwarf by 
studying a group of very very faint stars first discovered by 
michael r s hawkins of the royal observatory in edinburgh 
scotland 
we have measured the distance from earth to what seemed like 
the dimmest of these stars and found that the star is truly 
faint ianna said in a statement released by the foundation 
this supports the hypothesis that this whole group of stars is 
faint and contains other brown dwarf candidates 
some astronomers have suggested that brown dwarfs may be the 
socalled missing matter of the universe 
the missing matter question arose when astronomers studying the 
movement of stars and galaxies concluded that gravitation forces 
acting on visible stellar bodies are too great to be explained by 
the mass of the observed objects in space some believe that up to 
90 percent of the matter in the universe is not seen brown dwarfs 
it has been proposed could be part of the undetected matter 
there is also a theory that the missing mass is cold dark 
matter such as interstellar molecules black holes and a subatomic 
particles called neutrinos which cannot be observed 
ianna and bessell studied the candidate brown dwarf using an 
electronic camera on the onemeter telescope at the siding spring 
observatory 
sighting from two different perspectives within the earths 
orbit of the sun the scientists were able to calculate the 
distance of the object from earth the mass of the object was 
estimated based on studies of its luminosity or brightness 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP900329-0171 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the countrys top investigating agency 
thursday accused four former government officials of accepting 
bribes from airbus industrie to award a 147 billion contract to 
the european consortium 
the central bureau of investigation filed preliminary charges 
against ss sidhu the former aviation secretary rk prasad 
indian airlines former managing director kamini chadha another 
former managing director of the airline and former deputy managing 
director bk bhasin 
also accused were unidentified officials of airbus industrie 
based in toulouse france and international aero engines a 
company based in switzerland and east hartford conn it 
manufactured the v2500 engines used in the a320s 
under indian law preliminary charges are registered before the 
court and state that enough evidence exits to investigate final or 
regular charges are filed when investigations are completed 
the charges said the officials accepted kickbacks to reverse a 
decision to purchase usmade boeing 757 jetliners and instead buy 
38 airbus a320s they did not say how much the alleged kickbacks 
amounted to 
airbus officials in france said they had not been notified 
officially about the investigation they said they were surprised 
by the allegations and refused further comment 
the charges also said other public servants a term that would 
include politicians in office at the time of the alleged wrongoind 
were involved 
the bureau began investigating the deal completed in june 
after an indian airlines a320 crashed feb 14 while landing at the 
southern indian city of bangalore the crash killed 92 of the 146 
people on board 
prasad resigned after the accident 
the crash triggered criticism in the indian press it questioned 
the roles played by members of prime minister rajiv gandhis 
government in awarding the contract to airbus 
the previous government pushed through the deal with undue 
haste said india today a respected news magazine a month after 
the crash it ignored other options as well as warning signals 
about the inadequacy of the ground support system and brushed aside 
the need for more time to evaluate the aircraft 
indian newspapers said the bangalore crash was a result of the 
planes engines not responding in time to a computer command by the 
pilot when he found the aircraft was coming in too low for its 
landing 
it was the second crash involving an a320 the only passenger 
aircraft with computerized flight controls three people were 
killed in june 1988 when an a320 crashed during an airshow in 
france 
the government grounded all indian airlines a320s pending the 
report of a committee investigating the bangalore crash further 
deliveries of the plane have been halted 
the investigation is the third launched by prime minister vp 
singhs government into deals made by previous governments 
singh replaced rajiv gandhi as prime minister in december after 
triumphing in parliamentary elections he campaigned on a promise 
to end government corruption 
the central bureau of investigation is also inquiring into the 
purchase of artillery guns from the swedish company ab bofors and 
the purchase of submarines from the west german firm howaldt 
deutsche werke both have been clouded by allegations of kickbacks 
</TEXT>
