<TEXT>
the new legislature of the baltic republic estonia 
on thursday agreed to debate a more gradual path to restoring 
independence than that of lithuania a legislator said 
the supreme soviet of estonia on the first day of its session 
also elected arnold ruutel president of the republic reported the 
official soviet news agency tass ruutel is a former chairman of 
the legislatures presidium 
mart laar an independent deputy said in a telephone interview 
that the legislators friday are to debate a declaration saying the 
republic will work toward restoring the independence estonia 
enjoyed before it was annexed by the soviet union in 1940 
a second proposal calls for the legislature to cooperate with 
the estonian congress an informal group of 500 people that met 
earlier this month they consider themselves the real 
representative of estonians 
a bill calling for a transition to independence is on the 
agenda but the legislation probably will not be discussed friday 
laar said he said the length of the transition period so far has 
not been set 
tass said the proposals had been put forward by the estonian 
peoples front political movement which controls more than 40 of 
the 105 supreme soviet seats the legislators were elected in 
contested balloting march 18 
the estonian legislatures approach to restoring independence 
mirrors the path taken by the republics communist party meeting 
sunday the party established a sixmonth transition period to full 
independence from the soviet party 
estonians have taken a more cautious approach than lithuanians 
that baltic republic declared independence from moscow on march 11 
and it has been embroiled in a tense standoff with soviet 
authorities ever since 
estonian activists say they must act more cautiously because 
they do not have such large ethnic or legislative majorities as the 
lithuanians do in their republic the estonians also say they want 
to establish the conditions for independence before formally 
breaking with moscow 
the deputies also must elect a premier tass said a close 
election was expected between the current head of government 
indrik toome and the leader of the peoples front edgar savisaar 
