hoping to defuse weeks of tension with 
moscow lithuanias president has told citizens of the baltic 
republic not to resist if soviet troops tried to confiscate their 
weapons 
a deadline set by the kremlin passed wednesday without incident 
in the republic which has been at odds with moscow since it 
independence march 11 
both sides showed restraint wednesday with lithuania also 
shelving plans for border guards and the soviet army refraining 
from seizing more lithuanian buildings or rounding up more military 
deserters in the republic 
at present establishing border points would be stepping up 
