is by no means revolutionary 
but it is unique in that its from the same network that this 
year has given you sydney normal life city and his 
amp hers all examples of how not to commit comedy 
bagdad shows how to do it right not with a string of 
feeble oneliners but with believeable characters a fine cast and 
the awareness that the best humor often has the edge of sadness to 
it 
