democrats used to dine out on the old will 
rogers wisecrack i belong to no organized party i am a 
democrat 
the joke doesnt fit these days democrats are organizing all 
over the place choosing up sides and lining up in factions and 
caucuses but they cant get together on policy or on spokesmen to 
carry it to the voters their congressional majorities seem 
immobilized more often by intramural disputes than republican 
opposition 
theirs always has been a fractious coalition thats what rogers 
was joking about but they usually found ways to glue it together 
at campaign time sometimes they kept warring then they lost 
whats happening now is not so dramatic or clearly defined as 
the old battles over civil rights or the escalation of americas 
involvement in the war in vietnam in confrontations like those 
democrats acknowledged their unyielding differences on one point 
bargained over them then quietly collaborated on other matters 
their differences now are more mundane and the handling is more 
businesslike that wont necessarily make them easier to bridge 
the situation is a mirror image of the one republicans faced 25 
years ago out of power lacking a pulpit and a spokesman they 
dealt with it by creating the awkwardlynamed soontobeforgotten 
republican coordinating committee a panel of party leaders 
convened periodically to issue policy pronouncements 
