worked together on heart pumps for several years and their experts 
believe the batterypowered device is an important step forward 
currently such devices are powered by large airdriven pumps 
making movement difficult 
with this newer electrical pump you do have a wire through 
the skin but its battery controlled said frazier 
the heart assist pump or left ventricular assist device performs 
most of the pumping function of a normal hearts left ventricle 
many patients can live for months with such a device 
the batterypowered pump is vented to the outside through a 
small tube frazier said the only other part that passes through 
the skin is the wire that leads to the external battery worn under 
the patients arm 
