the accusations of excessive japanese influence have led to 
congressional hearings on tightening us control of foreign 
agents with emphasis on lobbyists for japanese business 
unlike the us congress japans parliament does not have 
institutionalized lobbies and influential japanese rarely accept 
requests to lobby on behalf of foreign interests 
the american tobacco pharmaceutical rice and electronics 
industries have offices working on their behalf in tokyo they and 
