polaroid corp which has been reorganizing since 
fending off a hostile takeover effort two years ago said thursday 
it would take additional steps to restructure itself to boost sales 
and respond better to market demands 
the reorganization is a major step in redirecting the company 
toward growth said i macallister booth president and chief 
executive of cambridgebased polaroid 
polaroid officials said the announcement caps a companywide 
restructuring polaroid undertook in 1988 while fighting a hostile 
takeover attempt by shamrock holdings 
key elements of the new organization are three business units 
family imaging business imaging and technical imaging that will 
focus on specific markets and product applications 
separately the company will create three major groups that will 
provide support in research sales and product development and 
manufacturing 
the executives overseeing the business units and support groups 
will report directly to a newly created office of the chief 
executive officer sheldon buckler polaroids executive vice 
president will join that office and share responsibilities with 
booth 
analysts said the changes are important because polaroid must 
show stronger sales growth 
polaroid earned 145 million last year compared with a 226 
million loss in 1988 during the takeover fight but sales grew only 
2 percent in 1989 to 19 billion 
analysts said the improved earnings resulted from cost cutting 
to have further increases in profits the company must accelerate 
its sales they said 
eugene glazer an analyst with dean witter reynolds inc said 
the new organization should help accomplish this task by making 
polaroid a more market driven company 
historically this company has been research driven he 
said adding that polaroids philosophy was great inventions 
create new markets 
