former control data corp chief robert price 
whose fouryear reign yielded 9239 million in net losses has 
received 424 million in retirement and severance pay and will get 
450000 a year under a threeyear consulting contract it was 
disclosed wednesday 
in addition price received 107 million in bonus income during 
the past 3 years under two separate stock award programs and 
possibly could get more bonus money under control datas longterm 
performance incentive plan 
his pension good for the rest of his life will bring another 
300000 a year 
the compensation was detailed in the companys annual proxy 
statement distributed wednesday to stockholders analysts and the 
media in advance of the companys may 2 annual shareholder meeting 
roger redmond a stock analyst for minneapolisbased piper 
jaffray amp hopwood inc said prices compensation is excessive 
considering the computer companys performance since price took 
control in january 1986 
lawrence perlman replaced price as chief executive officer in 
